# Overview

Next.js 16 + TypeScript + Drizzle + PostgreSQL (Supabase) + shadcn/ui + Tailwind CSS 4

## Stack

- **Framework:** Next.js 16 App Router, React 19
- **API:** tRPC v11, Zod v4, SuperJSON
- **Database:** PostgreSQL (Supabase), Drizzle
- **UI:** shadcn/ui, Tailwind CSS 4, Radix UI, CVA
- **Testing:** Vitest, Playwright

## Principles

1. tRPC-first (no Server Actions)
2. Strict TypeScript (no `any`)
3. Server Components default (`'use client'` only when needed)
4. Test everything (unit + E2E)
5. Remove code, don't deprecate

## Server vs Client

**Server (default):**

- Data fetching, backend access, security
- No `'use client'` directive

**Client (`'use client'`):**

- Event handlers, hooks, browser APIs
- Interactive UI, tRPC client queries
